edullary sponge kidney","Nephrocalcinosis","Perinephric abscess","Renal cyst formation"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EAcute pyelonephritis can lead to several serious complications. A \u003Cstrong\u003Eperinephric abscess\u003C/strong\u003E can develop when infection spreads beyond the kidney capsule into the surrounding tissue. This is a severe complication requiring urgent drainage and antibiotics.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe other options are not direct complications of pyelonephritis: \u003Cstrong\u003Erenal cyst formation\u003C/strong\u003E is typically genetic or acquired over time; \u003Cstrong\u003Eglomerular basement membrane thickening\u003C/strong\u003E is associated with diabetic nephropathy; \u003Cstrong\u003Emedullary sponge kidney\u003C/strong\u003E is a congenital condition; and \u003Cstrong\u003Enephrocalcinosis\u003C/strong\u003E results from disorders of calcium metabolism.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EOther important complications of acute pyelonephritis include sepsis, renal scarring, emphysematous pyelonephritis in diabetic patients, and renal papillary necrosis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Acute pyelonephritis is an infection of the renal parenchyma and collecting system that can lead to renal scarring and chronic kidney disease","Complications of acute pyelonephritis include perinephric abscess, sepsis, and renal papillary necrosis"],"references":["Sabih A, Leslie SW. Complicated Urinary Tract Infections. 2023 Nov 12. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 28613784","Bilsen MP, Jongeneel RMH, Schneeberger C, Platteel TN, van Nieuwkoop C, Mody L, Caterino JM, Geerlings SE, K\u00f6ves B, Wagenlehner F, Conroy SP, Visser LG, Lambregts MMC. Definitions of Urinary Tract Infection in Current Research: A Systematic Review. Open Forum Infect Dis. 2023 Jun 27;10(7):ofad332. doi: 10.1093/ofid/ofad332. PMID: 37426954; PMCID: PMC10323732","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51885"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15127"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51885","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51885"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-30T09:08:26+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-30T09:08:39+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7815"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66434"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4933","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4933"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd43","name":"Urinary","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:16:52+10:30","updatedA